00:01:39.089 --> 00:01:40.090
- And thank you,

00:01:40.090 --> 00:01:44.866
it's a pleasure to be here
in this fabulous symposium.

00:01:44.866 --> 00:01:46.860
I will be talking about mathematics

00:01:46.860 --> 00:01:50.930
and mathematics is perhaps
one of the most abstract,

00:01:50.930 --> 00:01:55.750
complex and precise human
conceptual systems ever invented.

00:01:55.750 --> 00:01:59.042
Think about the Euclidean
point, for example.

00:01:59.042 --> 00:02:02.210
It's an entity that has only one property,

00:02:02.210 --> 00:02:03.620
that's location.

00:02:03.620 --> 00:02:05.110
No extension whatsoever

00:02:05.110 --> 00:02:07.100
so no Euclidean point exists

00:02:07.100 --> 00:02:09.110
really objectively in the universe

00:02:09.110 --> 00:02:12.150
and we have no biology to
perceive a Euclidean point.

00:02:12.150 --> 00:02:15.270
Yet the Euclidean point,
the humble little guy,

00:02:15.270 --> 00:02:19.780
is the cornerstone of the
edifice of Euclidean geometry

00:02:19.780 --> 00:02:21.619
that led to analytic geometry,

00:02:21.619 --> 00:02:24.400
non-Euclidean geometries,
differential geometries,

00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:26.662
many other fields in mathematics.

00:02:26.662 --> 00:02:30.930
So one area that we could look at

00:02:30.930 --> 00:02:35.043
for the origins of this fabulous
human conceptual system,

00:02:35.043 --> 00:02:37.567
this abstract thing, is number.

00:02:37.567 --> 00:02:42.560
So to begin, consider the following.

00:02:42.560 --> 00:02:43.820
If you're presented, let's say,

00:02:43.820 --> 00:02:45.270
with this stimuli,

00:02:45.270 --> 00:02:47.973
it's very easy for us to
discriminate between them.

00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:50.885
But when the amount of dots increases,

00:02:50.885 --> 00:02:52.210
it's not as easy

00:02:52.210 --> 00:02:54.410
and we make a few more mistakes

00:02:54.410 --> 00:02:55.981
and we make confusions.

00:02:55.981 --> 00:02:58.143
Now the capacity to discriminate

00:02:58.143 --> 00:03:01.540
when there's only few of
them is called subitizing

00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:04.130
and has been studied by
experimental psychologists

00:03:04.130 --> 00:03:05.923
in the 1940s.

00:03:07.093 --> 00:03:10.160
So this is an ability we
don't need to go to school to

00:03:10.160 --> 00:03:13.480
and we share with many other species.

00:03:13.480 --> 00:03:16.210
Another ability is the following.

00:03:16.210 --> 00:03:17.960
If we're presented, let's say, with

00:03:19.270 --> 00:03:22.360
these groups of dots, black and white,

00:03:22.360 --> 00:03:25.040
when their proportions differ considerably

00:03:25.040 --> 00:03:26.470
it's very easy for us to say

00:03:26.470 --> 00:03:27.430
which one has more,

00:03:27.430 --> 00:03:30.670
even though we may not
know exactly how many

00:03:30.670 --> 00:03:31.804
but we can tell.

00:03:31.804 --> 00:03:34.391
When the proportions are
closer to each other,

00:03:34.391 --> 00:03:38.970
it's a little harder and
sometimes very, very difficult.

00:03:38.970 --> 00:03:41.070
So this capacity is referred to

00:03:41.070 --> 00:03:44.320
as large quantity discrimination.

00:03:44.320 --> 00:03:46.890
Now these two capacities we
share with many other species,

00:03:46.890 --> 00:03:48.090
as I was saying.

00:03:48.090 --> 00:03:50.230
So this has led to many,

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:53.560
really to believe that this
is about now mathematics.

00:03:53.560 --> 00:03:56.150
So you will tend to see many papers

00:03:56.150 --> 00:03:58.350
and chapters and academic material

00:03:58.350 --> 00:04:00.910
talking about monkey
mathematical abilities

00:04:00.910 --> 00:04:04.398
and kids in infancy without schooling

00:04:04.398 --> 00:04:08.270
and arithmetic occurring
at a single neuron level

00:04:08.270 --> 00:04:09.720
and so on and so forth

00:04:09.720 --> 00:04:12.770
all the way to more recently number,

00:04:12.770 --> 00:04:15.886
numerical cognition in
bees and other insects.

00:04:15.886 --> 00:04:17.900
Now of course, this is academia

00:04:17.900 --> 00:04:19.750
and then the media takes over

00:04:19.750 --> 00:04:22.280
and says well like the
New York Times here,

00:04:22.280 --> 00:04:24.480
science section earlier this year,

00:04:24.480 --> 00:04:25.740
many animals can count,

00:04:25.740 --> 00:04:27.096
some better than you.

00:04:27.096 --> 00:04:30.257
And I know there's some
individuals in power now

00:04:30.257 --> 00:04:33.440
who also say the New York
Times reporting fake news

00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:35.100
these days.

00:04:35.100 --> 00:04:36.770
But that's not the only one.

00:04:36.770 --> 00:04:39.270
Sometimes we see animals with tools

00:04:39.270 --> 00:04:40.940
and will kind of lead us to think

00:04:40.940 --> 00:04:43.081
that there's some
mathematical content involved

00:04:43.081 --> 00:04:44.795
or let's say this one,

00:04:44.795 --> 00:04:47.933
Fish as Good as College
Students in Number Test,

00:04:48.830 --> 00:04:52.080
and Mosquito Fish can Count up to 100

00:04:52.080 --> 00:04:53.840
and count in quotes.

00:04:53.840 --> 00:04:56.240
So the whole thing as a
package in this society,

00:04:56.240 --> 00:04:58.590
there's kind of a widely
accepted view that says,

00:04:58.590 --> 00:05:02.058
there's a biologically evolved
capacity that is specific

00:05:02.058 --> 00:05:03.790
for number and arithmetic

00:05:03.790 --> 00:05:07.850
and I will underline
here the word specific.

00:05:07.850 --> 00:05:10.840
Now of course, the question
is is it really the case?

00:05:10.840 --> 00:05:12.850
And it's been some debate more lately.

00:05:12.850 --> 00:05:14.140
And part of the issue is

00:05:14.140 --> 00:05:15.790
that some of these terms are policimous.

00:05:15.790 --> 00:05:17.950
Like number we use it for passport number,

00:05:17.950 --> 00:05:19.620
telephone number and many other things.

00:05:19.620 --> 00:05:21.670
So what do we really mean by number?

00:05:21.670 --> 00:05:23.980
And it turns out that in the literature,

00:05:23.980 --> 00:05:25.260
the scientific literature,

00:05:25.260 --> 00:05:29.770
is permeated really with
underspecified conceptions

00:05:29.770 --> 00:05:30.690
of what is numbers

00:05:30.690 --> 00:05:34.290
such that we can ascribe
numerical and arithmetical,

00:05:34.290 --> 00:05:37.460
mathematical capacities
to many other species.

00:05:37.460 --> 00:05:39.750
So let's examine this a little bit more.

00:05:39.750 --> 00:05:44.225
If we leave aside non-human
animals for a moment,

00:05:44.225 --> 00:05:49.145
we can focus on human data
that's been overlooked.

00:05:49.145 --> 00:05:52.560
For example, all known languages

00:05:52.560 --> 00:05:55.900
have natural quantifiers like
few, several, many and so on

00:05:55.900 --> 00:05:59.028
but by no means, they all
exhibit exact quantification.

00:05:59.028 --> 00:06:02.494
A recent study about 200
languages in aboriginal Australia

00:06:02.494 --> 00:06:05.020
from 13 different linguistic families

00:06:05.020 --> 00:06:06.155
showed that in fact,

00:06:06.155 --> 00:06:10.280
almost 90% of these languages

00:06:10.280 --> 00:06:14.870
do not have a numeral beyond
what we would call five.

00:06:14.870 --> 00:06:17.740
So you can't, in cultures
speaking these languages,

00:06:17.740 --> 00:06:21.750
refer to seven or 12 or 19 or 23.

00:06:21.750 --> 00:06:24.540
Now similar research has been found

00:06:24.540 --> 00:06:28.530
with hunter gatherers
in Australia and Africa

00:06:28.530 --> 00:06:29.670
and South America

00:06:29.670 --> 00:06:32.660
and I strongly recommend also
the book by Caleb Everett

00:06:32.660 --> 00:06:36.683
that goes more in depth analyzing
these particular cultures.

00:06:36.683 --> 00:06:38.070
Now the point is here

00:06:38.070 --> 00:06:41.050
that when we look at human language,

00:06:41.050 --> 00:06:44.451
language by itself really
does not lead to number

00:06:44.451 --> 00:06:47.040
beyond the subitizing range.

00:06:47.040 --> 00:06:50.460
So exact quantification
seems to be a cultural trait,

00:06:50.460 --> 00:06:52.494
not a biological trait.

00:06:52.494 --> 00:06:57.494
So how do we get from
perceiving, let's say these dots,

00:06:59.100 --> 00:07:03.500
to labeling them as let's
say being nine or eight,

00:07:03.500 --> 00:07:05.924
whether with spoken words or with digits?

00:07:05.924 --> 00:07:07.410
Well when we do that,

00:07:07.410 --> 00:07:10.460
we're involved in what is
called symbolic reference.

00:07:10.460 --> 00:07:13.920
It's not just a purely
psychophysical perception anymore.

00:07:13.920 --> 00:07:17.340
It's now another cognitive
activity like symbolic reference.

00:07:17.340 --> 00:07:20.680
And we could do this with
many other types of numerals

00:07:20.680 --> 00:07:22.950
like in Spanish nueve and ocho

00:07:22.950 --> 00:07:26.230
or we could do Roman
numerals and other forms

00:07:26.230 --> 00:07:27.860
and different bases in mathematics

00:07:27.860 --> 00:07:29.980
or infinite decimal notation, if you like,

00:07:29.980 --> 00:07:31.900
and so on and so forth.

00:07:31.900 --> 00:07:33.613
And there's another important property.

00:07:33.613 --> 00:07:36.050
It's their relational inoperable.

00:07:36.050 --> 00:07:38.190
So like my laptop computer here says

00:07:38.190 --> 00:07:43.190
number eight is equivalent to
the product of two and four,

00:07:43.260 --> 00:07:45.210
it's one more than seven and those things.

00:07:45.210 --> 00:07:47.260
So they're all related to each other.

00:07:47.260 --> 00:07:51.264
So really our familiar
list, one, two, three,

00:07:51.264 --> 00:07:54.320
has very specific abstract properties,

00:07:54.320 --> 00:07:56.200
like it quantifies exactly,

00:07:56.200 --> 00:07:57.383
not in an approximate way,

00:07:57.383 --> 00:08:01.760
and it is abstract,
transcending stimulus modality,

00:08:01.760 --> 00:08:03.160
visual or auditory,

00:08:03.160 --> 00:08:05.280
it has a cardinal sense, an ordinal sense,

00:08:05.280 --> 00:08:08.450
a relational property that we just saw,

00:08:08.450 --> 00:08:10.991
combinative, operable,
and most importantly,

00:08:10.991 --> 00:08:13.870
referred to symbolically.

00:08:13.870 --> 00:08:17.960
So the number really is exact
symbolic quantification.

00:08:17.960 --> 00:08:19.678
And this seems to be quite different

00:08:19.678 --> 00:08:22.815
from what we observe,
let's say with trained,

00:08:22.815 --> 00:08:26.530
by humans of course,
trained animals in the lab

00:08:26.530 --> 00:08:28.237
where you can get, for example, monkeys

00:08:28.237 --> 00:08:32.520
in painstaking training,
four months, 20,000 trials,

00:08:32.520 --> 00:08:36.080
to discriminate dots in
a ratio three to four

00:08:36.080 --> 00:08:39.410
only to 70% of accuracy.

00:08:39.410 --> 00:08:42.180
So it seems to be that we're
in a different realm here.

00:08:42.180 --> 00:08:43.800
So to summarize here,

00:08:43.800 --> 00:08:45.570
we can look at this figure.

00:08:45.570 --> 00:08:47.010
Essentially what we have

00:08:47.010 --> 00:08:49.920
is amount of discrete
stuff, let's say dots,

00:08:49.920 --> 00:08:51.739
going from center to periphery,

00:08:51.739 --> 00:08:54.030
increasing in amount.

00:08:54.030 --> 00:08:57.665
So what you see in the bottom left here,

00:08:57.665 --> 00:09:01.840
what you have is subitizing a
large quantity discrimination,

00:09:01.840 --> 00:09:04.150
the two abilities we just exercised

00:09:04.150 --> 00:09:05.242
a little bit at the beginning,

00:09:05.242 --> 00:09:08.268
and we share those with many species.

00:09:08.268 --> 00:09:10.749
Now with symbolic reference,

00:09:10.749 --> 00:09:13.270
there's a symbolic gap there,

00:09:13.270 --> 00:09:17.140
we can then label things
like natural quantifiers

00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:19.190
like many, few and so on,

00:09:19.190 --> 00:09:21.360
and then with exact quantification

00:09:21.360 --> 00:09:24.215
we get into what you see
clockwise there in blue

00:09:24.215 --> 00:09:27.130
which is now truly numerical.

00:09:27.130 --> 00:09:28.985
So the point is here,

00:09:28.985 --> 00:09:31.384
what you see on the left

00:09:31.384 --> 00:09:34.029
is really about quantity perception.

00:09:34.029 --> 00:09:36.250
It's quantical abilities that we,

00:09:36.250 --> 00:09:38.270
it's biologically endowed.

00:09:38.270 --> 00:09:40.674
But in order to really get to number

00:09:40.674 --> 00:09:44.130
we need to go across
the symbolic reference

00:09:44.130 --> 00:09:47.060
and that is not biologically evolvable.

00:09:47.060 --> 00:09:49.720
So here I'm gonna borrow
a quote from Terri Deacon,

00:09:49.720 --> 00:09:51.370
also a member of Carta,

00:09:51.370 --> 00:09:54.410
who says, "Symbolic reference
must be acquired by learning,"

00:09:54.410 --> 00:09:56.747
so this occurs in the
anthology of individuals,

00:09:56.747 --> 00:09:59.177
"and lacks both the natural associations

00:09:59.177 --> 00:10:01.627
"and transgenerational
reproductive consequences

00:10:01.627 --> 00:10:03.177
"that would make such references

00:10:03.177 --> 00:10:05.210
"biologically evolvable."

00:10:06.080 --> 00:10:08.147
So exact symbolic quantification

00:10:08.147 --> 00:10:10.540
beyond the subitizing range

00:10:10.540 --> 00:10:12.338
really needs a whole apparatus,

00:10:12.338 --> 00:10:17.260
a culture that actually cares
about being exact and precise.

00:10:17.260 --> 00:10:19.240
So motivated by cultural preoccupations,

00:10:19.240 --> 00:10:22.560
tracking valuables, trading,
accounting and so on.

00:10:22.560 --> 00:10:25.320
And this supported by
and enhanced by tools

00:10:25.320 --> 00:10:27.079
and off-loading cognition

00:10:27.079 --> 00:10:30.155
which requires enculturation.

00:10:30.155 --> 00:10:31.900
Of course, part of that comes

00:10:31.900 --> 00:10:34.150
and we heard already
previously about this,

00:10:34.150 --> 00:10:37.090
the invention of writing
about 6,000 years ago.

00:10:37.090 --> 00:10:38.850
Initially, according to many authors

00:10:38.850 --> 00:10:40.539
coming from tokens,

00:10:40.539 --> 00:10:43.170
tokens printed on envelope of clay

00:10:43.170 --> 00:10:46.292
and eventually leading to clay tablets.

00:10:46.292 --> 00:10:49.040
But you could also have,

00:10:49.040 --> 00:10:50.790
in the absence of writing, for example,

00:10:50.790 --> 00:10:55.380
like the Inca did with
the use of the apos,

00:10:55.380 --> 00:10:58.836
doing performing amazingly
sophisticated calculations

00:10:58.836 --> 00:11:00.497
without writing

00:11:00.497 --> 00:11:04.720
or what you see in Oceania,
in Papua New Guinea,

00:11:04.720 --> 00:11:07.223
many groups, you have
now grammatical tools

00:11:07.223 --> 00:11:10.638
in the language that
could for example codify

00:11:10.638 --> 00:11:12.920
certain types of morphines

00:11:12.920 --> 00:11:14.960
that would characterize
number of quantities

00:11:14.960 --> 00:11:16.580
for counting things you care about.

00:11:16.580 --> 00:11:18.420
For example, in this case,

00:11:18.420 --> 00:11:19.490
as you see in the picture,

00:11:19.490 --> 00:11:24.490
yams in the culture Nen,
work done by Nick Evans.

00:11:24.947 --> 00:11:27.150
So what's in common there

00:11:27.150 --> 00:11:30.380
is that you need a
conventionalized symbolic reference

00:11:30.380 --> 00:11:32.913
for exact quantification.

00:11:33.790 --> 00:11:38.223
Now when there is number,

00:11:38.223 --> 00:11:42.160
most number systems are in base five or 10

00:11:42.160 --> 00:11:43.780
and you would say, "Why is that?"

00:11:43.780 --> 00:11:46.757
Well, here we have a very handy tool

00:11:46.757 --> 00:11:48.470
all of a sudden in front of us,

00:11:48.470 --> 00:11:49.890
you can identify fingers

00:11:49.890 --> 00:11:52.410
and we can sort of,
they're readily available.

00:11:52.410 --> 00:11:54.850
So that could explain part of it.

00:11:54.850 --> 00:11:57.530
The issue is that gorillas, chimpanzees

00:11:57.530 --> 00:12:00.030
and many species, raccoons,

00:12:00.030 --> 00:12:01.393
they also are pentadactyl,

00:12:01.393 --> 00:12:03.150
they also have five fingers.

00:12:03.150 --> 00:12:04.600
So evolution there,

00:12:04.600 --> 00:12:06.282
giving that particular form.

00:12:06.282 --> 00:12:08.070
So we have that,

00:12:08.070 --> 00:12:09.280
we have brains that control

00:12:09.280 --> 00:12:10.520
and get all the inputs, et cetera,

00:12:10.520 --> 00:12:12.430
but what we don't have in these cases,

00:12:12.430 --> 00:12:14.370
is symbolic reference

00:12:14.370 --> 00:12:16.930
and the capacity to actually use this

00:12:16.930 --> 00:12:18.900
as now potential tools

00:12:18.900 --> 00:12:21.480
which doesn't come with a handbook.

00:12:21.480 --> 00:12:23.173
Cultural variations exist

00:12:23.173 --> 00:12:26.240
in how you actually use
the hand for counting.

00:12:26.240 --> 00:12:28.970
So here you have top right number eight,

00:12:28.970 --> 00:12:31.940
being characterized by
manually, unimanually,

00:12:31.940 --> 00:12:33.300
sometimes using the finger,

00:12:33.300 --> 00:12:36.240
sometimes using the finger joints.

00:12:36.240 --> 00:12:38.760
So number eight, if you use finger joints

00:12:38.760 --> 00:12:41.810
and the tip would be this,
for example, and so on

00:12:41.810 --> 00:12:42.809
in some cultures.

00:12:42.809 --> 00:12:46.890
Now, when there is written
exact symbolic number,

00:12:46.890 --> 00:12:48.830
it seems all this to be mediated

00:12:48.830 --> 00:12:52.530
by culturally shaped cortical,
phenotypical plasticity.

00:12:52.530 --> 00:12:55.270
According to this work by
Tang et. al, for example,

00:12:55.270 --> 00:12:59.750
they presented digits to English speakers

00:12:59.750 --> 00:13:01.540
and Chinese native speakers

00:13:01.540 --> 00:13:02.380
and they just asked

00:13:02.380 --> 00:13:04.090
to do very simple calculations.

00:13:04.090 --> 00:13:06.900
And what we observe is
very different recruitment

00:13:06.900 --> 00:13:09.734
for neural populations in the two groups.

00:13:09.734 --> 00:13:13.599
You see more recruitment
in the left hemisphere

00:13:13.599 --> 00:13:17.330
(mumbles) area in the English speakers,

00:13:17.330 --> 00:13:20.070
and much, let's say, more
in the premotor regions

00:13:20.070 --> 00:13:21.740
for the Chinese speakers.

00:13:21.740 --> 00:13:22.910
So number then,

00:13:22.910 --> 00:13:27.060
really what we have,
is a language-mediated,

00:13:27.060 --> 00:13:30.400
conventionalized, exact
symbolic quantification

00:13:30.400 --> 00:13:32.240
which is a cultural trait.

00:13:32.240 --> 00:13:34.850
And this occurrying quite, quite recently

00:13:34.850 --> 00:13:39.220
and largely outside of
biological evolution.

00:13:39.220 --> 00:13:42.870
So it builds on biologically
evolved preconditions.

00:13:42.870 --> 00:13:45.960
We need subitizing and large
quantity discrimination

00:13:45.960 --> 00:13:49.440
but themselves, they're not
mathematical or numerical.

00:13:49.440 --> 00:13:52.210
So these are motivated by
cultural preoccupations,

00:13:52.210 --> 00:13:53.043
as I said,

00:13:53.043 --> 00:13:55.660
supported crucially by
material and conceptual tools

00:13:55.660 --> 00:13:59.195
and the biology that makes
enculturation possible.

00:13:59.195 --> 00:14:01.550
So I want to take this
now to the next step.

00:14:01.550 --> 00:14:02.680
Once we have numbers,

00:14:02.680 --> 00:14:04.572
we can start creating all
kinds of other things.

00:14:04.572 --> 00:14:09.428
One very ubiquitous, powerful
tool is a number line

00:14:09.428 --> 00:14:11.690
which now we need another system

00:14:11.690 --> 00:14:15.050
which is to conceive numbers
as locations in space,

00:14:15.050 --> 00:14:16.610
metaphorically, if you will.

00:14:16.610 --> 00:14:17.443
And this of course,

00:14:17.443 --> 00:14:18.740
many of the talks before this,

00:14:18.740 --> 00:14:20.900
when we're using graphs to characterize

00:14:20.900 --> 00:14:22.000
some mounds and so on,

00:14:23.192 --> 00:14:26.980
it's helpful for reading economic graphs

00:14:26.980 --> 00:14:29.210
and look at scientific data

00:14:29.210 --> 00:14:31.230
or develop vector spaces

00:14:31.230 --> 00:14:33.967
and fancy visualizations and so on.

00:14:33.967 --> 00:14:35.190
What is interesting

00:14:35.190 --> 00:14:36.581
is that these days,

00:14:36.581 --> 00:14:40.540
this is learned or
presented in kindergarten.

00:14:40.540 --> 00:14:43.483
So kindergarteners already
start to see little bunnies

00:14:43.483 --> 00:14:45.650
jumping back and forth and froggies

00:14:45.650 --> 00:14:48.221
doing jumps and so on and so forth.

00:14:48.221 --> 00:14:50.190
So this has led a lot of people

00:14:50.190 --> 00:14:52.030
to think that perhaps we have,

00:14:52.030 --> 00:14:54.900
again, a biologically
endowed mental number line

00:14:54.900 --> 00:14:57.030
which is housed in the
intraparietal sulcus

00:14:57.030 --> 00:14:58.113
of the human brain.

00:14:59.030 --> 00:15:01.380
Well that's true if you
only look at westerners

00:15:01.380 --> 00:15:02.820
who already went to school

00:15:02.820 --> 00:15:04.950
and have done all this work.

00:15:04.950 --> 00:15:08.270
So a lot of papers support the idea

00:15:08.270 --> 00:15:10.580
that you would have very
spontaneous mappings

00:15:10.580 --> 00:15:12.680
and occurring in infants and macaques

00:15:12.680 --> 00:15:15.215
and more recently a paper in Science

00:15:15.215 --> 00:15:18.070
saying that newborn chicks now,

00:15:18.070 --> 00:15:21.064
so go figure, what kind
of cortex they would have,

00:15:21.064 --> 00:15:25.023
would actually have a mental
number line like humans.

00:15:25.023 --> 00:15:27.606
Now if that were really the case,

00:15:27.606 --> 00:15:30.450
let's cross that with
some other type of data.

00:15:30.450 --> 00:15:33.260
For example, we would expect culture,

00:15:33.260 --> 00:15:36.280
number-savvy cultures
like Babylonia, let's say,

00:15:36.280 --> 00:15:39.410
to have some manifestation
of number lines somewhere

00:15:39.410 --> 00:15:41.405
in all the number crunching they did.

00:15:41.405 --> 00:15:43.620
Well, when you look at
half a million tablets

00:15:43.620 --> 00:15:44.460
that we know today,

00:15:44.460 --> 00:15:46.859
there's not a single number line there.

00:15:46.859 --> 00:15:48.250
So that says something.

00:15:48.250 --> 00:15:50.950
They did a lot of numbers
without a number line.

00:15:50.950 --> 00:15:54.480
In fact, you have to go to 17th century,

00:15:54.480 --> 00:15:56.920
it's not even in La
Geometrie by Rene Descartes

00:15:57.920 --> 00:15:59.730
who invented analytic geometry,

00:15:59.730 --> 00:16:01.543
not a single number line there either.

00:16:01.543 --> 00:16:04.590
There first appears to be,

00:16:04.590 --> 00:16:06.960
John Napier when he's
introducing algorithms,

00:16:06.960 --> 00:16:08.341
a very sophisticated notion

00:16:08.341 --> 00:16:11.950
and he is saying, okay, here's a line,

00:16:11.950 --> 00:16:13.605
we're gonna start thinking this way.

00:16:13.605 --> 00:16:17.270
But the first who does the
operational use of a number line

00:16:17.270 --> 00:16:18.147
is John Wallis.

00:16:18.147 --> 00:16:21.010
And here, if you really
look at the text it says,

00:16:21.010 --> 00:16:24.430
okay, the audience is
(speaking in foreign language),

00:16:24.430 --> 00:16:26.240
the top of the top of mathematicians

00:16:26.240 --> 00:16:27.925
in Europe in the 17th century saying,

00:16:27.925 --> 00:16:30.680
think of a man walking five steps

00:16:30.680 --> 00:16:32.190
and then walking two back

00:16:32.190 --> 00:16:35.450
and that's gonna be five
minus two equals three.

00:16:35.450 --> 00:16:37.760
That's what you hear today
in a kindergarten class

00:16:37.760 --> 00:16:40.473
but this is now a few
hundred years ago in Europe.

00:16:40.473 --> 00:16:42.377
So we also wanted to test

00:16:42.377 --> 00:16:44.080
how spontaneous is this?

00:16:44.080 --> 00:16:45.540
So we went, we did a study

00:16:45.540 --> 00:16:47.730
among the Yupno of Papua New Guinea,

00:16:47.730 --> 00:16:50.025
and we presented a line segment

00:16:50.025 --> 00:16:52.340
and following other methods

00:16:52.340 --> 00:16:54.697
that have been used in the Amazon,

00:16:54.697 --> 00:16:57.080
and we could see that for example,

00:16:57.080 --> 00:17:00.550
even though they had
numbers to at least 20,

00:17:00.550 --> 00:17:01.577
and numerals,

00:17:01.577 --> 00:17:06.012
they essentially mapped
small numbers on one end

00:17:06.012 --> 00:17:08.030
and bigger to the other end,

00:17:08.030 --> 00:17:10.916
whether it was dots or
tones or other things

00:17:10.916 --> 00:17:13.350
unlike the schooled Yupno

00:17:13.350 --> 00:17:15.810
and California controls.

00:17:15.810 --> 00:17:17.850
As you can see, on the right side.

00:17:17.850 --> 00:17:19.390
So the red one being the unschooled

00:17:19.390 --> 00:17:22.390
using only the extremes.

00:17:22.390 --> 00:17:25.010
So no use of the path whatsoever

00:17:25.010 --> 00:17:26.840
which is required for the number lines.

00:17:26.840 --> 00:17:28.650
So the intrusion doesn't seem to be,

00:17:28.650 --> 00:17:31.081
again, universal in that sense.

00:17:31.081 --> 00:17:33.620
So what do we do with these abstractions?

00:17:33.620 --> 00:17:34.923
Well, we do crazy things.

00:17:34.923 --> 00:17:36.757
So of course, we have the mathematicians

00:17:36.757 --> 00:17:39.229
very recently developing it

00:17:39.229 --> 00:17:42.733
but today is introduced
in the kindergarten class.

00:17:44.027 --> 00:17:48.460
But this could be taken
to further directions

00:17:48.460 --> 00:17:50.780
to develop the notions of hyperreal lines.

00:17:50.780 --> 00:17:52.100
So all of a sudden now,

00:17:52.100 --> 00:17:53.830
the number line and the real line

00:17:53.830 --> 00:17:56.310
which is now housing irrational numbers

00:17:56.310 --> 00:17:57.680
and rational numbers

00:17:57.680 --> 00:17:59.690
and by virtue of least upper bound axon,

00:17:59.690 --> 00:18:01.820
you have a complete order field,

00:18:01.820 --> 00:18:04.600
no more thoughts could fit in there.

00:18:04.600 --> 00:18:07.530
Well you can when you go
to non Euclidean umbers.

00:18:07.530 --> 00:18:10.020
Infinitely, tiny,
infinitely small numbers,

00:18:10.020 --> 00:18:11.620
the absolons you see there,

00:18:11.620 --> 00:18:14.930
or huge numbers, their
reciprocals, the omegas,

00:18:14.930 --> 00:18:17.791
that are bigger and larger
than any real number.

00:18:17.791 --> 00:18:20.470
So then you start to have embedded,

00:18:20.470 --> 00:18:22.337
mutually incompatible, non-commensurable,

00:18:22.337 --> 00:18:26.000
number lines embedded
in infinitely many spots

00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:28.250
in infinitely many of these lines.

00:18:28.250 --> 00:18:31.660
All this going back to
the simple number line

00:18:31.660 --> 00:18:33.554
that we develop about 300 years ago.

00:18:33.554 --> 00:18:36.770
So really the story of numbers

00:18:36.770 --> 00:18:38.300
and tools and mathematics

00:18:38.300 --> 00:18:41.060
can be reduced to this
process of enculturation

00:18:41.060 --> 00:18:43.110
where you do need an
a biological apparatus

00:18:43.110 --> 00:18:44.170
that would support it.

00:18:44.170 --> 00:18:45.950
So I would like to close with this quote,

00:18:45.950 --> 00:18:48.767
and I thank Pascal Gagneur
for pointing me to this one,

00:18:48.767 --> 00:18:51.027
by geneticist and evolutionary biologist,

00:18:51.027 --> 00:18:52.986
Theodosius Dobzhansky who said,

00:18:52.986 --> 00:18:55.647
"Human evolution has two components,

00:18:55.647 --> 00:18:57.867
"the biological or organic,

00:18:57.867 --> 00:18:59.781
"and the cultural or superorganic.

00:18:59.781 --> 00:19:02.587
"These components are
neither mutually exclusive

00:19:02.587 --> 00:19:03.447
"nor independent

00:19:03.447 --> 00:19:06.337
"but interrelated and interdependent.

00:19:06.337 --> 00:19:08.627
"Human evolution cannot be understood

00:19:08.627 --> 00:19:10.847
"as a purely biological process,

00:19:10.847 --> 00:19:12.757
"nor can it be adequately described

00:19:12.757 --> 00:19:14.397
"as a history of culture.

00:19:14.397 --> 00:19:17.600
"It is the interaction
of biology and culture."

00:19:17.600 --> 00:19:21.180
And I think mathematics
exemplifies this perfectly well.

00:19:21.180 --> 00:19:22.013
Thank you.

00:19:22.013 --> 00:19:24.768
(audience applause)

